hints.description: This global company roasts and sells high-quality coffee beans and beverages, along with complementary food items like pastries and sandwiches. Founded in Seattle, it operates a vast network of company-owned and licensed stores worldwide, offering a "third place" experience between home and work. Howard Schultz is a key figure in its history, significantly shaping its growth and expansion.
hints.funFact1: Initially, the company was named after a literary character  a sailor in Herman Melvilles *Moby Dick*, and the first store was designed to resemble a nautical trading post.
hints.funFact2: The company has experimented with various loyalty programs over the years, but its current rewards system, launched in 2019, is personalized and uses machine learning to offer tailored promotions and recommendations to its members.
